<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Richard Rubin's Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some economic comparisons between 1992, George Bush's last year  
in office, and the present, after six years of the Clinton 
administration. 
</P>
<P>
	Gross Domestic Product -- 1992: 2.7 percent annual growth; 1998:  
3.9 percent growth. 
</P>
<P>
	Unemployment -- 1992: 7.5 percent; 1998: 4.5 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Consumer Price Index -- 1992: up 2.9 percent from the previous  
year; 1998: up 1.6 percent from previous year. 
</P>
<P>
	Federal Budget -- 1992: $290.4 billion deficit; 1998: $69.2  
billion surplus. 
</P>
<P>
	Dow Jones industrial average -- Jan. 19, 1993: 3,255; May 12,  
1999: 11,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
