<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Spielberg To Preview Fla. Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Steven Spielberg, Ron Howard and Michael  
Douglas were among the celebrities on hand for a preview of 
Universal Studios' newest theme park, Islands of Adventure. 
</P>
<P>
	Although the 110-acre park doesn't open until May 28, Universal,  
and its partner, London-based The Rank Group, have been giving a 
preview to hundreds of reporters, analysts and company executives 
this week. 
</P>
<P>
	``I continue to be amazed by what everyone has accomplished  
here,'' Spielberg said during a ceremony Wednesday. Spielberg 
served as the park's creative consultant. 
</P>
<P>
	``Making a theme park is like making movies and plays and then  
building an entire city to contain them,'' he said. ``The hopeful 
result is the same as in the movies. We just want people to be 
dazzled and entertained.'' 


</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
