<HEADLINE> Teacher Allegedly Strips in Class </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A substitute teacher has been arrested for  
allegedly taking off his pants in front of a class of fourth 
graders and asking children to touch his genitals. 
</P>
<P>
	Wendell Smith appeared dazed and was possibly hyperventilating  
after Wednesday's alleged incident at the El Sereno Elementary 
School, another teacher told police. He was evaluated at a hospital 
and found to be healthy. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith, 46, had worked for the Los Angeles Unified School  
District as a substitute for two years without incident. He was 
arrested for investigation of sexual misconduct. 
</P>
<P>
	``He told a girl to come here ... if she wanted to touch him,''  
said pupil Stephanie Lewandowski. ``Then he got another girl and he 
touched her bottom, he was trying to put his hand in her pants.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith grabbed a boy, but the boy kicked him, she said.  
</P>
<P>
	``And another got a ball and hit him in the face with it so he  
would stop and he didn't,'' she said. 
</P>
