<HEADLINE> NBA Names All-Defensive Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Now, only Michael Jordan can be considered a  
better defender than Scottie Pippen. 
</P>
<P>
	On Thursday, the Houston forward became only the third player  
selected at least eight times for the NBA's All-Defensive team, 
joining Bobby Jones and Jordan. A former Pippen teammate with the 
Chicago Bulls, Jordan was a nine-time choice. 
</P>
<P>
	Guard Gary Payton of the Seattle SuperSonics made it for the  
sixth time. 
</P>
<P>
	Also voted to the team by the league's 29 coaches were forwards  
Tim Duncan of the San Antonio Spurs and Karl Malone of the Utah 
Jazz, center Alonzo Mourning of the Miami Heat and guard Jason Kidd 
of Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
	Six players were selected because of a tie in the voting between  
forwards Pippen and Malone. 
</P>
<P>
	Chosen for the second-team were forwards P.J. Brown of Miami and  
Theo Ratliff of the Philadelphia 76ers, guards Mookie Blaylock of 
the Atlanta Hawks and Eddie Jones of the Charlotte Hornets, and 
center Dikembe Mutombo of Atlanta. 
</P>
