<HEADLINE> San Miguel, Marubeni Mull Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MANILA, Philippines (AP) -- Philippine food and beverage giant  
San Miguel Corp. said Thursday it has started talks with the major 
Japanese trading company Marubeni Corp. to explore possible joint 
ventures. 
</P>
<P>
	In a statement to the stock exchange, San Miguel said the talks  
began on May 6 but that no agreement had yet been reached with 
Marubeni ``on any specific area of collaboration or joint 
venture.'' 
</P>
<P>
	San Miguel last year raised more than $1 billion from the sale  
of its investments in Coca-Cola Beverages and Nestle Philippines 
Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	San Miguel chairman Eduardo Cojuangco said the company will use  
the proceeds from the sale to pay some debts and to reinvest in San 
Miguel's core businesses -- food, packaging and beverages. 
</P>
<P>
	San Miguel has breweries in China, Hong Kong, Indonesia and  
Vietnam. 
</P>
