<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
	ConAgra Inc., up 2 11/16 at 27 1/2.  
</P>
<P>
	The agricultural company said it will cut its work force by  
7,000 employees and expects to record an initial charge of $420 
million in the fourth quarter on a new restructuring plan. 

</P>
<P>
	KeyCorp, up 2 at 36 15/16.  
</P>
<P>
	National City Corp., up 1 at 72 1/8.  
</P>
<P>
	KeyCorp rose for the second day in a row on rumors National City  
would acquire the Cleveland-based banking corporation. Both 
companies declined comment. 

</P>
<P>
	Gap Inc., down 3/16 at 62 1/16.  
</P>
<P>
	The retail clothing company reported per-share earnings of 34  
cents, up from 22 cents a year ago. But sales at stores open at 
least a year grew by 11 percent, down from 17 percent last year. 
Analysts said Gap and other merchants were hurt by this year's 
early Easter holiday. 

</P>
<P>
	Daniel Industries Inc., up 1 3/8 at 20 15/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Emerson Electric Co., down 2 5/8 at 67 1/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Emerson agreed to buy Daniel for about $460 million. In a joint  
press release Thursday, the companies said Emerson will make a cash 
tender offer of $21.25 a share for Daniel's common shares. 

</P>
<P>
	Bank One Corp., up 2 5/8 at 61 1/8.  
</P>
<P>
	First USA, a unit of Bank One, acquired Carolina First Corp.'s  
$112 million in credit-card receivables for an undisclosed amount. 
The deal represents about 130,000 Visa credit-card accounts. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
	J.B. Hunt, down 3 3/4 at 19 5/32.  
</P>
<P>
	The trucking company said competition had cut into its shipping  
traffic and that April revenues, which did not meet expectations, 
will hurt second-quarter profits. 
                                                                  
</P>
<P>
	Matrix Pharmaceutical Inc., up 3 15/32 at 6 7/32.  
</P>
<P>
	The company late Wednesday said it got fast-track review status  
from the Food and Drug Administration for its IntraDose Injectable 
Gel, a cancer treatment. 

</P>
<P>
	Lycos, up 11/16 at 107 11/16.  
</P>
<P>
