<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Radio Shack: RCA Video Products Only </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tandy Corp. has chosen Thomson Consumer  
Electronics' RCA line to be the exclusive brand of audio and video 
products sold at its Radio Shack stores, the companies announced 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Tandy will phase out its house brands of electronics -- known  
under the Optimus and Realistic names -- in the next year and 
replace them entirely with RCA goods. 
</P>
<P>
	The RCA products, which include televisions, stereos and DVD  
players, will be showcased in a special merchandising area -- or a 
store within a store -- in at least 4,000 of Radio Shack's 
company-owned stores by the second quarter of the year 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	Radio Shack has similar agreements with Sprint for wireless  
phones and Compaq Computer for home computers. Tandy says that both 
relationships have helped boost store traffic and sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomson is a subsidiary of Thomson Multimedia, a leading  
electronics manufacturer with products sold under the RCA, Thomson, 
GE, Proscan, Telefunken and Saba brands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
