<HEADLINE> Minn. Capitol Evacuated Over Threat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) -- The state Capitol was evacuated Thursday  
afternoon and legislative meetings halted after a bomb threat was 
called into Gov. Jesse Ventura's office. No bomb was found. 
</P>
<P>
	The governor and lieutenant governor were taken out of the  
building at about 3 p.m. The building was reopened about 90 minutes 
later. 
</P>
<P>
	A male caller threatened to blow up the building, said Public  
Safety Commissioner Charlie Weaver. 
</P>
<P>
	Because of the threat, Weaver said access to the building will  
be limited and packages checked until the end of the legislative 
session next week. 
</P>
