<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Cher, singer, actress, artist.  
</P>
<P>
	Personal stats: Cherilyn Sarkisian was born May 20, 1946, in El  
Centro, Calif. She met Salvatore ``Sonny'' Bono, a backup singer 
and aspiring songwriter, while she was a teen-ager. 
</P>
<P>
	``When I was 16, I met Sonny,'' she has recalled. ``I never saw  
anything like him before in my life. He walked into this room and I 
swear to God, I saw him and everybody else was washed away.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The pair clicked as Sonny and Cher with a string of hits,  
beginning with ``I Got You Babe'' in 1965. They hosted their own 
television variety program, ``The Sonny and Cher Comedy Hour,'' 
from 1971-1974. Bono's Dutch-boy haircut, droopy mustache and 
bell-bottom trousers contrasted with Cher's thin, towering figure, 
draped in spectacularly sequined outfits. 
</P>
<P>
	Their daughter, Chastity, was born in 1969.  
</P>
<P>
	After divorcing Bono in 1974, Cher married rocker Gregg Allman  
and gave birth to a son, Elijah. She continued to pursue her 
singing and acting career, interspersed with exercise video and 
infomercial ventures. 
</P>
<P>
	Her film roles include ``Come Back to the Five and Dime, Jimmy  
Dean, Jimmy Dean,'' ``Mask,'' ``The Witches of Eastwick'' and 
``Suspect.'' She won an Academy Award for best actress for her role 
in the 1987 film, ``Moonstruck.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Her latest film is Franco Zeffirelli's ``Tea With Mussolini,''  
which also stars Judi Dench, Joan Plowright and Maggie Smith. Her 
new album, ``Believe,'' features the best-selling single of the 
same name. She is also the author of ``The First Time.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote:* ``Artists don't become artists out of something that's  
good. Artists become artists out of something that's not good. It's 
something you're trying to fill up, trying to make up for. That's 
why artists are nuts.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays May 16-22:  
</P>
<P>
	May 16: Actor Pierce Brosnan is 46. Actress Debra Winger is 44.  
Actress Mare Winningham is 40. Singer Janet Jackson is 33. Actress 
Tracey Gold is 30. Actor David Boreanaz (``Buffy the Vampire 
Slayer'') is 28. Actress Tori Spelling is 26. 
</P>
<P>
	May 17: Actor-director Dennis Hopper is 63. Singer Taj Mahal is  
57. Actor Bill Paxton is 44. Actor-comedian Bob Saget is 43. Singer 
Enya is 38. Singer-musician Trent Reznor of Nine Inch Nails is 34. 
Musician O'Dell of Mint Condition is 34. Singer Jordan Knight of 
New Kids on the Block is 29. Singer Darnell Van Rensalier of Shai 
is 29. Singer Kandi Burruss of Xscape is 23. Actor Tahj Mowry 
(``Smart Guy'') is 13. 
</P>
<P>
	May 18: Singer Perry Como is 87. Actor Bill Macy is 77. Actor  
Robert Morse is 68. Actor Dwayne Hickman (``The Many Loves of Dobie 
Gillis'') is 65. Country singer George Strait is 47. 
Singer-musician Page Hamilton of Helmet is 39. Rapper Special Ed is 
25. Singer Darryl Allen of Mista is 19. 
</P>
<P>
	May 19: Musician Pete Townshend of The Who is 54.  
Singer-musician Dusty Hill of ZZ Top is 50. Singer Joey Ramone of 
The Ramones is 47. Musician Iain Harvie of Del Amitri is 37. Singer 
Jenny Berggren of Ace of Base is 27. Actor Eric Lloyd (``Jesse'') 
is 13. 
</P>
<P>
	May 20: Singer Joe Cocker is 55. Singer-actress Cher is 53.  
Actor Bronson Pinchot is 40. Actor Tony Goldwyn is 39. Actress 
Mindy Cohn (``Facts of Life'') is 33. Musician Tom Gorman of Belly 
is 33. Rapper Busta Rhymes is 27. 
</P>
<P>
	May 21: Musician Bill Champlin of Chicago is 52. Singer Leo  
Sayer is 51. Actor Mr. T is 47. Actor Judge Reinhold is 42. 
</P>
<P>
	May 22: Actor Richard Benjamin is 61. Actor Paul Winfield is 58.  
Singer Morrissey is 40. Musician Dan Roberts of Crash Test Dummies 
is 32. Actress Alison Eastwood (``Midnight in the Garden of Good 
and Evil'') is 27. Actress A.J. Langer (''It's Like, You Know 
...'') is 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
