<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Yields on 10-Year Notes Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Yields on ten-year Treasury notes rose in  
Wednesday's auction to the highest level in about a year. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield was 5.510 percent, up from 4.913 percent at the last  
auction on Feb. 10. It was the highest rate since ten-year notes 
sold for 5.646 percent on May 13, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 5.5 percent with  
each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,992.30. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of $12 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling  
$19.5 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
