<HEADLINE> Clintons To Vacation in Florida </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton and first lady Hillary  
Rodham Clinton are taking a Florida vacation later this month, the 
White House announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	White House press secretary Joe Lockhart said the Clintons would  
stay at White Oak Plantation from May 25 to May 30. White Oak is a 
conservation center and retreat in Yulee, Fla., on the state's 
north Atlantic coast. 
</P>
<P>
	Chelsea Clinton, a sophomore at Stanford University, was not  
expected to accompany her parents on the trip, according to the 
first lady's office. 
</P>
<P>
	White Oak is near Amelia Island, where Clinton and Vice  
President Al Gore attended a $50,000 per couple fund-raising 
retreat for the Democratic Party in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
