<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Higher; Gold Up Also </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar rose against other major currencies in  
European trading today. Gold also was higher. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0620, down from $1.0683 Wednesday. The  
dollar was quoted at 121.42 Japanese yen, up from 121.29 yen. At 
midday in New York, the euro was quoted at $1.0627 and the dollar 
was quoted at 121.82 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Wednesday: 1.5022 Swiss  
francs, up from 1.5014; 1.4614 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4578. 
The British pound was quoted at $1.6186, down from $1.6204. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.8416 German marks, up from 1.8308; 
6.1766 French francs, up from 6.1402; 2.0751 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.0628; 1,823.23 Italian lire, up from 1,812.48. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $277.30 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$276.60 on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the gold market was closed for a holiday on Thursday.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold rose $0.80 in Hong Kong to close at $278.75.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.45 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$5.35. 
</P>
</TEXT>
