<HEADLINE>  Relief Efforts Hampered in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KUKES, Albania (AP) -- A lack of coordination among NATO, aid  
groups and the Albanian government has bedeviled efforts to move 
100,000 Kosovo refugees out of this dusty, overcrowded border 
region, a U.N. official said today. 
