<HEADLINE> N.J. Jackals Re-Sign Pete Rose Jr. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LITTLE FALLS, N.J. (AP) -- The Northern League's New Jersey  
Jackals re-signed outfielder Pete Rose Jr. today. 
</P>
<P>
	The 29-year-old son of baseball's career hits leader played in  
12 games last year with the Jackals after signing as a free agent 
Aug. 5, hitting .424 with one home run, four doubles and eight 
RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	He was sidelined with a foot injury for almost three weeks last  
year. 
</P>
<P>
	Taken by the Baltimore Orioles in the 12th round of the 1988  
amateur draft, Rose played parts of two seasons at Triple-A with 
the Cincinnati Reds and Pittsburgh Pirates. He appeared in 11 major 
league games with the Reds in 1997, going 2-for-14 (.143) with two 
runs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
