<HEADLINE> Texas Refinery Blast Injures 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- An explosion at a gasoline refinery  
injured at least 10 people, five of them critically, and prompted 
authorities to advise residents to stay indoors. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire at Coastal Corp. was contained around noon Thursday  
after burning for about an hour. Authorities said the fire involved 
naphtha -- a petroleum product and solvent -- but did not produce 
toxic smoke. 
</P>
<P>
	Explosions shook the walls of buildings in nearby neighborhoods.  
Emergency management officials did not evacuate the area, but told 
residents to shut their doors and windows and remain indoors. 
</P>
<P>
	Ten people were admitted to Spohn Memorial Hospital, spokeswoman  
Rita Patrick said. Five were in critical condition and five were in 
satisfactory condition, but other details were not released. 

</P>
