<HEADLINE> Severed Fingered Printed for Clues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Prints from a severed finger were  
being used to track down the gunmen who shot and killed the owner 
of an auto body shop before fleeing in a car. 
</P>
<P>
	Detectives discovered the finger inside Bowen Auto Body, where  
Spurgeon Bowen, 47, was shot Wednesday while arguing with three 
men, police said. It was unclear what started the dispute. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators were not sure how the finger was cut off. They are  
using its print to search for the gunman who apparently lost it and 
the others involved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
