<HEADLINE> Bio of Treasury Secretary Nominee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NAME -- Lawrence H. Summers.  
</P>
<P>
	AGE-BIRTH DATE -- 44. Born Nov. 30, 1954, in New Haven, Conn.  
</P>
<P>
	EDUCATION -- Massachusetts Institute of Technology, S.B., 1975;  
Harvard University, Ph.D., 1982. 
</P>
<P>
	EXPERIENCE -- MIT faculty, 1979-1982; Domestic policy economist  
on President Reagan's Council of Economic Advisors, 1982-1983; 
Harvard professor of economics, 1983-1993; World Bank chief 
economist, 1991-1993; Undersecretary of the Treasury for 
International Affairs, 1993-1995; Deputy Treasury Secretary, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	FAMILY -- Wife, Victoria Summers, a tax attorney; children, twin  
daughters and a son. 
</P>
</TEXT>
