<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Helps Conyers Raise Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton continued thanking his  
impeachment defenders Thursday at an appearance at a fund-raiser in 
honor of Rep. John Conyers of Michigan, the ranking Democrat on the 
House Judiciary Committee. 
</P>
<P>
	``I appreciate the fact that in standing up for me last year, he  
stood up for the Constitution of the United States,'' Clinton said. 
</P>
<P>
	The event, celebrating Conyers' 70th birthday, raised $225,000  
for the ``Conyers for Congress'' committee. Clinton also thanked 
Conyers for supporting his economic policies, fighting for human 
rights abroad and civil rights at home. 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton was careful to express contrition and avoid gloating  
after his acquittal in the Senate impeachment trial. But he began 
to publicly show his gratitude to his defenders in March, when he 
appeared at events honoring Democratic Rep. Max Sandlin of Texas 
and former Sen. Dale Bumpers of Arkansas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
