<HEADLINE> Teacher Allegedly Stripped in Class </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A substitute teacher was arrested Thursday  
for allegedly taking off his pants in front of a class of fourth 
graders and asking children to touch his genitals. 
</P>
<P>
	Wendell Smith appeared dazed and was possibly hyperventilating  
after Wednesday's alleged incident at the El Sereno Elementary 
School, another teacher told police. 
</P>
<P>
	He was evaluated at a hospital and found to be healthy.  
</P>
<P>
	Smith, 46, of Los Angeles, had worked for the Los Angeles  
Unified School District as a substitute for two years without 
incident. He was arrested for investigation of sexual misconduct. 
</P>
<P>
	``He told a girl to come here ... if she wanted to touch him,''  
said pupil Stephanie Lewandowski. ``Then he got another girl and he 
touched her bottom, he was trying to put his hand in her pants.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith grabbed a boy, but the boy kicked him, she said.  
</P>
<P>
	``And another got a ball and hit him in the face with it so he  
would stop and he didn't.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Student Stacy Vallejo said classmates were scared.  
</P>
<P>
	``He said, `Come here, come here ... to his privates. But we  
said `No,''' Stacy said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
