<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-13 14:05:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gore To Outline Education Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Vice President Al Gore plans to deliver an  
education address Sunday in Iowa, the first in a series of speeches 
designed to outline his agenda for the 2000 presidential campaign. 
</P>
<P>
	He is delivering the commencement address at Graceland College  
in Lamoni, Iowa, as part of a weekend of campaigning in the state 
that conducts the first caucuses of the 2000 presidential race. 
</P>
<P>
	Aides say the topic will be education.  
</P>
<P>
	In the next few months, Gore will deliver about six speeches on  
issues that will be cornerstone of his campaign to succeed 
President Clinton. One adviser compared the strategy to Clinton's 
in 1992, when he delivered a series of policy address early in his 
presidential campaign. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
