<HEADLINE> President of Scripps Named Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- William R. Burleigh, president of The E.W.  
Scripps Co., has been named chairman of the media company. 
</P>
<P>
	Burleigh, 63, a board member since 1990, will continue as  
president and chief executive officer. He took on those jobs in 
1996. 
</P>
<P>
	As chairman, he succeeds Lawrence A. Leser, who decided not to  
seek re-election. Leser was chairman for nearly five years, and 
president and chief executive from 1985 to 1994. He had been a 
board member since 1977. 
</P>
<P>
	Burleigh, whose new position was announced Thursday, is a former  
vice chairman of The Associated Press board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
	Nackey E. Scagliotti, president and publisher of Neighborhood  
Publications Inc., was elected to the Scripps board during the 
annual shareholders meeting. Neighborhood Publications is a weekly 
newspaper group based in Bedford, N.H. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Scagliotti is a niece of Charles E. Scripps, chairman of  
the executive committee of the Scripps board. She is also board 
chairman for the Manchester, N.H.-based Union Leader Corp., which 
publishes daily and Sunday newspapers. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the Scripps company's holdings are 19 daily newspapers,  
nine network-affiliated television stations and two cable 
television networks -- Home &AMP; Garden Television and the Food 
Network. 

</P>
</TEXT>
