<HEADLINE> Actor Discusses Star Wars Creature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- You can't tell what Ahmed Best looks like from  
watching the computer-generated character he plays in the latest 
``Star Wars'' movie. But you'll get to know him just the same. 
</P>
<P>
	``All the sound effects, all the voices, it's all me,'' the  
25-year-old Best said in a recent interview. ``My face won't be in 
it. But my face will be in something else. I've come to terms with 
it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Best plays Jar Jar Binks, a floppy-eared, two-legged creature in  
``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Best spoke all of Jar Jar's lines, invented his reptilian noises  
and physically acted out the scenes, but he was ultimately replaced 
with a computer image. 
</P>
<P>
	``Everybody else had to be serious, but I could be funny,'' he  
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
