<HEADLINE> Texas Refinery Explosion Injures 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- An explosion at a refinery plant  
Thursday injured at least ten people. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire at Coastal Corp. was contained around noon, after  
burning for about an hour, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said the fire involved naphtha -- a petroleum product  
and solvent -- but did not produce toxic smoke. 
</P>
<P>
	Emergency management officials did not evacuate the area, but  
told local residents to shut their doors and windows and remain 
indoors. 
</P>
<P>
	Ten people were admitted to a hospital.  


</P>
