<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Low pressure over Illinois brought rain to the Midwest and  
Mid-Atlantic regions of the country on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers were scattered across Minnesota and Iowa, into the Ohio  
Valley and Mid-Atlantic states. Heavy rains were reported in parts 
of Illinois and Indiana. 
</P>
<P>
	Fair to partly cloudy skies over the Tennessee Valley and  
Southeast developed into scattered storms over those areas. 
</P>
<P>
	High pressure over much of the central United States brought  
fair, dry weather with some clouds over the Dakotas and northern 
Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers, along with mountain snow fell on parts of the northern  
Rockies and Pacific Northwest. 
</P>
<P>
	The steadiest precipitation was reported over Montana, southern  
Idaho and Wyoming. Fair, dry weather was reported in the Southwest 
and southern Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a morning low of 21  
degrees in Saranac Lake, N.Y., to an afternoon high of 86 degrees 
in Las Vegas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
