<HEADLINE> Tyson's Wife Says He Has Soft Side </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- There's a soft side of Mike Tyson reserved for  
family, his wife says. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's human, he has a family, he's sweet, he's real loving and  
kindhearted,'' Dr. Monica Turner Tyson said in the latest Esquire. 
``In the ring, he's a warrior, but at home he's a big teddy bear.'' 
</P>
<P>
	At 32, the former heavyweight champion has two children -- a  
1 1/2-year-old son, Amir, and a 3-year-old daughter, Rayna. 
</P>
<P>
	``He always says that he takes the punches so his kids don't  
have to,'' his wife said. ``He loves his children so much, it's 
like they're his whole world now.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Tyson is serving a one-year jail sentence for assaulting two  
motorists in Maryland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
