<HEADLINE> Kathie Lee To Debut on Broadway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- If it's Tuesday, it must be time for Kathie Lee  
Gifford. 
</P>
<P>
	The co-host of television's ``Live with Regis and Kathie Lee''  
is scheduled to make her Broadway debut this November, replacing 
Carol Burnett in ``Putting It Together'' for one night each week. 
</P>
<P>
	Burnett opens Oct. 28 at the Ethel Barrymore Theater in the  
revue of songs from Stephen Sondheim musicals, but she won't play 
most Tuesday evenings. 
</P>
<P>
	Gifford's first performance in the show will be Nov. 9. Also  
starring in the revue, which includes songs from such Sondheim 
musicals as ``Company,'' ``Follies'' and ``A Little Night Music,'' 
will be Bronson Pinchot of the old television sitcom ``Perfect 
Strangers'' and George Hearn, last seen on Broadway in ``Sunset 
Boulevard.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Putting It Together'' was first done in 1993 off-Broadway with  
Julie Andrews as its star. 
</P>
