<HEADLINE> Man Pleads to Pay Telephone Scam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- One of two men charged in a scheme that bilked  
investors out of $20 million pleaded guilty Thursday to charges of 
racketeering conspiracy and wire fraud. 
</P>
<P>
	Scott Holmberg, 34, faces five years and one month in federal  
prison under a plea deal with prosecutors that also requires him to 
testify against alleged coconspirator, Slobodan Lunic. 
