<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Alma Mater Names Theater After Uhry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Playwright Alfred Uhry has a new honor -- his own  
high school theater. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's amazing -- like an out-of-body experience,'' said the  
Oscar-winning author of ``Driving Miss Daisy.'' 
</P>
<P>
	His alma mater, Druid Hills High School, is renaming its  
470-seat auditorium the Alfred Uhry Theater. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's as if there's this other fellow, Alfred Uhry, who gets  
all this praise, and then there's me, the lucky stiff who gets to 
come along and enjoy the ride,'' Uhry said. 
</P>
<P>
	Uhry graduated from the high school in 1954. His most recent  
work, the musical ``Parade,'' has been nominated for a Tony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
