<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 23 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened higher. The Dow Jones  
industrial average is up 23 points in today's early going. 
Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 8-5 lead over 
decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 16 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up two points. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street has been put in a good mood thanks to some favorable  
economic news. 
</P>
<P>
	The government reported an increase in producer prices of one  
half percent for April. 
</P>
<P>
	And while that is higher than in recent months, it's still in  
line with analysts' expectations. 
</P>
<P>
	And nearly all the increase came in the energy sector.  
</P>
<P>
	At the same time, retail sales rose a modest one tenth percent,  
as auto sales sagged. 
</P>
<P>
	The economic figures were well-received in the Treasury market,  
sending bond prices sharply higher. 
</P>
